  "texts": [
    "At the same time, other research shows that users didn't experience the feeling of looseness of the authorship while working with an AI agent (Singh et al., 2023).",
    "This correlates with Yang et al. (2022), where users estimated AI to be an active writer in the collaborative process rather than simply a passive AI writing assistant.",
    "Collaborative writing contributes to students' learning outcomes and prepares them for teamwork (Fiialka et al., 2021).",
    "Given the scientists' opinions and our study's results, we believe that the role of AI depends on the type of text generation system (for example, Wordcraft & ChatGPT) and the expectations of the human author regarding interaction.",
    "Interaction with a chatbot can also be viewed from the perspective of improving writing skills and enhancing writers' mastery (Calderwood et al., 2020)."
